<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Error - GA4 Analytics Data Bundle Demo</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            padding-top: 20px;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col">
                <h1>Error</h1>
                <p class="lead">An error occurred while fetching analytics data</p>
                <a href="{{ path('demo_index') }}" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">Back to Home</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white">
                        Error Details
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>{{ error }}</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4">Possible Causes</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Missing or invalid service account credentials</li>
                            <li>Missing or invalid property ID</li>
                            <li>Service account does not have access to the GA4 property</li>
                            <li>API quota exceeded</li>
                            <li>Network connection issues</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4">Troubleshooting Steps</h5>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Check that your environment variables are correctly set:
                                <ul>
                                    <li><code>ANALYTICS_PROPERTY_ID</code></li>
                                    <li><code>ANALYTICS_CREDENTIALS_PATH</code></li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>Verify that the credentials file exists and is accessible</li>
                            <li>Make sure the service account has at least "Viewer" access to the GA4 property</li>
                            <li>Check that the Google Analytics Data API is enabled in your Google Cloud project</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>